# =============================================================================
# GuitarHub Environment Variables
# =============================================================================
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in values for local development:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# All variables are OPTIONAL unless marked REQUIRED. The application provides
# sensible defaults for development.

# ── GitHub / CI ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# GitHub token used for publishing artifacts and creating GitHub issues
# (e.g., health check reports). Not needed for local scrape runs.
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Run ID injected by GitHub Actions. Falls back to "local" in development
# when not set.
# GITHUB_RUN_ID=local

# Repository in "owner/repo" format (e.g., "WillSanCaZam/guitarhub"). Injected by
# GitHub Actions. Needed for health check issue creation.
# GITHUB_REPOSITORY=WillSanCaZam/guitarhub

# ── Database / Storage ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Path to the SQLite database file. Defaults to "guitarhub.db" in the
# working directory.
# GUITARHUB_DB_PATH=guitarhub.db

# Optional override for the directory containing migration SQL files.
# Defaults to src-tauri/src/repository/sqlite/migrations/ relative to the
# crate manifest.
# GUITARHUB_MIGRATIONS_DIR=./migrations

# ── Source Adapters ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Each source adapter (scraper/adapters/sources/*.py) may declare a
# REQUIRED_ENV tuple. When set, the adapter validates the var exists at
# import time. Document those vars below.
#
# Example (Reverb):
#   REVERB_API_KEY — Required when the Reverb adapter is loaded.
#   REVERB_API_KEY=your_key_here
#
# Example (MercadoLibre):
#   MERCADOLIBRE_APP_ID — Optional; enables authenticated API access.
#   MERCADOLIBRE_APP_ID=your_app_id
#
# Example (Guitarras Co):
#   None — public scraping only.
